    <chapter xml:id="ch_intro">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <p>
        A vector is a quantity with magnitude and direction. A scalar is a quantity with magnitude only.
 
      </p>

      <p> Vector quantities have two characteristics, a magnitude and a direction. Scalar quantities have only a magnitude.
        https://www.grc.nasa.gov/www/k-12/airplane/vectors.html
      </p>
      <p> 
        Vectors can be represented by directed line segments. The length of the line represents the magnitude. The direction of the line represents the direction.

      </p>
      <p>
        <term>Scalars</term> have magnitude. <term>Vectors</term> have magnitude and direction.</p>

